                                        Background Concept about SSRF


● Server Side Request Forgery (SSRF) refers to an attack where in an attacker is able to
send a crafted request from a vulnerable web application.



                                        Impact of SSRF


● Abuse trust
● Bypass ip whitelisting
● Bypass host based authentication
● Read resource
● Scan the internal network


                                       How to Hunt for SSRF


● You have to find any parameter that may have some kind of
external interaction or they can interact to external domain

Example :

● Any.com/index/php?uri=http://external.com



